attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, no section header

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is a MIPS variant of the Mozi IoT botnet. It propagates by exploiting multiple known vulnerabilities, including D-Link HNAP command injection (`/HNAP1/`cd`) and various UPnP/SOAP-based exploits. The malware achieves persistence by modifying startup scripts like `/etc/rc.local` and `/etc/init.d/S95baby.sh`, and by remounting the filesystem as read-write (`mount -o remount,rw /overlay /`). It also manipulates `iptables` to open ports for C2 or peer-to-peer communication. IOCs include numerous download and execute commands for payloads named after architectures, e.g., `/Mozi.m` and `/Mozi.a`.
